es","Short posterior ciliary arteries","Anterior ciliary arteries"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior ciliary arteries\u003C/strong\u003E are the main vessels supplying the conjunctiva, episclera and iris. They arise from the muscular branches of the ophthalmic artery and pierce the sclera near the corneal limbus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecentral retinal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the inner layers of the retina, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Emuscular arteries\u003C/strong\u003E supply the extraocular muscles. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elong posterior ciliary arteries\u003C/strong\u003E supply the ciliary body and form the major arterial circle of the iris, and the \u003Cstrong\u003Eshort posterior ciliary arteries\u003C/strong\u003E supply the choroid and ciliary processes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The anterior ciliary arteries supply the conjunctiva, episclera and iris, arising from muscular branches of the ophthalmic artery.","The ophthalmic artery enters the orbit through the optic canal alongside the optic nerve and gives multiple branches to supply ocular structures."],"references":["Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Bird B, Stawicki SP. Anatomy, Head and Neck, Ophthalmic Arteries. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29493942","Probst, L., \u0026 Tsai, J. (2024). Ophthalmology: Clinical and Surgical Principles. CRC Press","Salmon, J. F. (2024). Kanski\u0027s Clinical Ophthalmology E-Book: A Systematic Approach. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kels BD, Grzybowski A, Grant-Kels JM. Human ocular anatomy. Clin Dermatol. 2015 Mar-Apr;33(2):140-6. doi: 10.1016/j.clindermatol.2014.10.006. PMID: 25704934"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"984